  "text_preview": "ASL park ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► American Sign Language: \"park\" The right sign for \"park\" depends on what you mean . If you mean \"park\" as in \"park a car\": See: PARK-car See: PARKING- LOT See: PARKING PERMIT If you mean \"park\" as in \"a place of recreation\" then you should fingerspell P-A-R-K: If you are talking about an area of land that has trees then you can use the sign \"FOREST\" which is a pluralized version of TREE . FOREST = PARK-(version) See: FOREST If you mean \"park\" as in an \"amusement park\" then you could sign ENJOY and spell P-A-R-K, but really in the Deaf World we rarely use the phrase \"amusement park.\" Instead we just tend to refer to a few specific parks to establish that we are talking about \"that\" type of park. I've seen some of my friends "
